nd walked to the smithy's barn.  There Hippolyte told her to chose any weapons.  Something that she would feel comfortable with and ready.  There were still warriors left in the city.  And they would stand with Ara in case of attack.  <br>
<br>
Ara stepped into the smithy and looked over the weapons.  Two slender long curved swords caught her eyes.  She had fought with the very same type in Rome as a slave.  Arahuta walked over and slide them from their places in the wooden wall then stepped back.  Instantly, like an old habit unable to be rid of, she began to move and twist with the swords in hand.  Fighting off the invisible enemy.  Then with a nod, she knew she was ready.  <br>
<br>
Arahuta went to her hut and fashioned two scabbards for the long thin blades.   Once finished she walked out of her hut and sat on the steps.  Listening for the call of the cities gaurdians, for anything. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualcippe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alcippe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#993300>(8/21/01 6:16:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Following</span><hr size=1> She sat unsure, watching her queen and listening to her words.   Ready and willing, Aclippe's heart beat to aid her amazon athelfi.  Dressed in her war leathers, weapons at her side, she chanted in her head to the Goddesses.  o0 be with me and my sisters, keep us steady and strong 0o<br>
When Hippolyte called them to ride, young Alcippe followed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#993300>(8/21/01 6:53:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Following</span><hr size=1> ::Sartha's voice let out a warcry as Hippolyte and her other Athelfi began to ride. She then whistled to send Vela on towards battle in Scynthia. She would fight alongside her sisters as always::<br>
